<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TPal2">
<l>koḻuṅkoṭi mullaiyiṉ koḻumala raṇavik kūrntatu kuṇaticai māruta mituvō</l>
<l>eḻuntaṉa malaraṇaip paḷḷikoḷ ḷaṉṉa mīṉpaṉi naṉaintata miruñciṟa kutaṟi</l>
<l>viḻuṅkiya mutalaiyiṉ pilampurai pēḻvāy veḷḷeyi ṟuṟavataṉ viṭattiṉuk kaṉuṅki</l>
<l>aḻuṅkiya vāṉaiyi ṉaruntuyar keṭutta varaṅkattam māpaḷḷi yeḻuntaru ḷāyē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Is this the wind from the eastern direction that [blows] abundantly</l>
<l>embracing the plump flowers of the flourishing wild jasmine creepers?</l>
<l>The haṃsas that slept in the beds of flower have risen</l>
<l>flapping their big wings moistened by the dew that was brought forth.</l>
<l>O Lord of Raṅgam</l>
<l>—who destroyed the hard[-to-bear] affliction of the elephant in distress,</l>
<l>which, as the white teeth in the cave-like large mouth of the devouring crocodile sank in,</l>
<l>suffered pain from its poison—</l>
<l>do grace to wake up from sleep!</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
